SORGHUM ERGOT - MEXICO, USA
****************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
Date: Thu, 13 May 1999 14:24:05
From: dick hamilton <rhamilto@direct.ca>
Source: EPPO Reporting Service, Paris, 1999-03-01
No. 3

Details are given on the spread of _Claviceps africana_ in
Mexico. In addition to Guanajuato, Jalisco, Michoacan and
Tamaulipas, the fungus also occurs in San Luis Potosi, Sinaloa
and Veracruz states [i.e. central Mexico & the East Coast up to the
border with Texas].
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@usa.healthnet.org>
[The disease has since spread to the USA and was recorded in
Texas and Kansas in 1997. The disease is a serious constraint in
the production of F1 hybrid seed, an essential element in
productive sorghum cultivation systems worldwide - Mod.DH]
..........................................rh/jw
